On 11/12/2012 7:47 PM, Jack L Stone wrote:
> As an update on Rosie's request for help yesterday on who might have
> displayed our private list archives to an open site, we have succeeded
> in taking down the site and now hot on the trail of the offender. The
> host of that site understood the problem and seriousness of the
> offense and cooperated immediately.
>
> We know how the couple of thousand messages where placed there. It was
> taken by a person who logged in and took copies without asking
> permission. Thus, we have purged the member list of the A-D archives,
> leaving in some selected members. The rest have been removed and if
> any on this list are members, just re-register.
>
> Thanks to those, on and offlist, who tried to politely and kindly
> help.....
>
> BTW: We frequently receive requests to use some of our material and
> permission is usually granted if it serves a good purpose. Some are
> for translation into other languages. We don't mind sharing if at
> least we are asked permission to do so first.
